\section{Experiments}
\label{sec:experiments}
%==============================================================================
\subsection{Training Setup}
Table~\ref{tab:training} summarizes the training configuration. For CNNs we minimize cross-entropy loss with mini-batch SGD; we use Adam (default), AdamW, or SGD with momentum as ablations. Learning rate and weight decay are fixed per run; we use a cosine annealing learning-rate schedule over the training epochs. For classical models we fit SVM and logistic regression on the full (standardized) training set after HOG extraction.

